  The Startup-failsafe
  ====================

  This script is located in the "S" drawer. Its purpose is to boot 
  only a minimal subset of components in order to provide a more 
  robust and safe environment to carry out maintenance and 
  troubleshooting operations. 
  
  This special purpose Startup-failsafe script will only be executed 
  at startup if either the user agreed to do it when booting without a 
  68040/60 library when their systems required one, or by selecting 
  the "Failsafe boot" check box in the Amiga Early Startup Menu, which 
  can be accessed by holding both mouse buttons at boot or by keeping 
  the HELP key depressed when booting.
  
  The following features have been disabled for Startup-failsafe 
  operation:

  Extra floppy buffers, 680x0.library check, HappyENV, auto-mounting 
  of DOSDrivers, special display drivers, Expansion drawer-based 
  drivers, Console clipboard, ARexx, Saved preferences loading & use. 

  Also the WBStartup folder won't have its contents processed and the 
  User-startup won't be executed either.
  
  The following is a breakdown of AmigaOS 3.2 Startup-failsafe script 
  along with comments describing what each section does. Don't be 
  alarmed if it does not exactly match yours. This example is only 
  meant to provide you with a general overview of what is involved.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  FailAt 10
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Sets the failure tolerance limit within this script for commands to 
  the default value.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  SetPatch >NIL:
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Applies several patches and fixes to many OS components. Since we 
  don't like to have the list shown, it is redirected to NIL:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Version >NIL:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Initializes the Kickstart and Workbench variables.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  MakeDir RAM:T RAM:ENV
  Copy ENVARC: RAM:ENV QUIET ALL NOREQ
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Creates several temporal directories. 
  It also copies the contents of ENVARC: to ENV:
  In this way they become faster since they end up in RAM.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Assign ENV: RAM:ENV
  Assign T: RAM:T

  FailAt 21
  Assign PRINTERS: DEVS:Printers
  Assign KEYMAPS: DEVS:Keymaps
  Assign LOCALE: SYS:Locale
  Assign LIBS: SYS:Classes ADD
  Assign HELP: LOCALE:Help DEFER
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Generates multiple Assigns required for proper OS usage.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  AddDataTypes REFRESH QUIET
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Initializes system data types.
  
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Path C: SYS:Utilities SYS:Rexxc SYS:System S: SYS:Prefs SYS:Tools SYS:Tools/Commodities
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Defines the access path for programs so that they can be directly 
  run from the CLI/Shell without having to specify their exact 
  location.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  LoadWB SKIP
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Loads Workbench but does not process the WBStartup drawer contents.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Wait 1
  RequestChoice "                  ATTENTION!" "You have booted into Failsafe mode.*nSeveral features have been disabled.*n*nThis is a safe environment to carry out*nmaintenance and troubleshooting tasks." "OK" >NIL:
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Waits till Workbench loads and displays a message to inform users.

----------------------------------------------------------------------  
  EndCLI >NIL:
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Closes the current CLI/Shell interface.
  